  @skip
  Scenario: [12] Aggregation of named paths
    Given an empty graph
    And having executed:
      """
      CREATE (a:A), (b:B), (c:C), (d:D), (e:E), (f:F)
      CREATE (a)-[:R]->(b)
      CREATE (c)-[:R]->(d)
      CREATE (d)-[:R]->(e)
      CREATE (e)-[:R]->(f)
      """
    When executing query:
      """
      MATCH p = (a)-[*]->(b)
      RETURN collect(nodes(p)) AS paths, length(p) AS l
      ORDER BY l
      """
    Then the result should be, in order:
      | paths                                                    | l |
      | [[(:A), (:B)], [(:C), (:D)], [(:D), (:E)], [(:E), (:F)]] | 1 |
      | [[(:C), (:D), (:E)], [(:D), (:E), (:F)]]                 | 2 |
      | [[(:C), (:D), (:E), (:F)]]                               | 3 |
    And no side effects

